data.description:
Revalidate App - Terms and Conditions
Last updated: 30/05/2024

1. Acceptance of Terms
By downloading, installing, or using the Revalidate app ("the App"), you agree to comply with and be bound by the terms and conditions outlined herein. If you do not agree with these terms, please refrain from using the App.

2. Basic Rules for the App
a. You must provide accurate and up-to-date information during the registration process, it is advised that personally identifiable information (PII) is omitted.
b. The App is intended for use by healthcare practitioners for the purpose of tracking and managing their revalidation process.
c. You are not obligated or contracted to use the App, and you may deactivate the app at any time.
d. You agree not to engage in any unauthorised use of the App, including but not limited to attempting to access data that does not belong to you.
e. The App is only available on Android and iOS mobile platforms.

3. Confidentiality and User Responsibility
a. Users are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of their account credentials and ensuring their security.
b. The questions and materials used in the App are sourced from the Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) and other government bodies for guidance purposes. Users are not permitted to reproduce, distribute, or create derivative works from these materials.
c. Users acknowledge that the speed and functionality of the App are dependent on internet provider and Wi-Fi connection. Service levels may vary accordingly.
d. Storage of data within the App is the user's responsibility. Revalidate takes reasonable measures to protect the security and privacy of user data, but users should be diligent in ensuring the accuracy and completeness of their recorded information.
e. Users are responsible for managing their login passwords and securing their device's locking screens.

4. Recording Other People's Personal Data
a. Users are not advised or permitted to record other people\'s personal data, such as names or email addresses, within the App.
b. Revalidate is not responsible for any unauthorised recording or storage of third-party personal data by users.
c. Users are urged to respect the privacy and data protection rights of others and refrain from entering or storing unauthorised personal information within the App.

5. Disclaimers and Limitations of Liability
a. The App is provided "as is" and "as available" without any warranties, expressed or implied.
b. Revalidate disclaims all liability for any errors, inaccuracies, or omissions in the information provided by the App.
c. In no event shall Revalidate be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of your use or inability to use the App.
d. Revalidate is not responsible for any disruptions, errors, or delays in the operation of the App.

6. Data Security and Privacy
a. Revalidate takes reasonable measures to protect the security and privacy of your data. However, we cannot guarantee the security of information transmitted through the App.
b. You acknowledge and agree that Revalidate may collect and use certain information as outlined in our Privacy Policy. By using the App, you consent to the collection and use of your information as described therein.

7. App not Responsible for Revalidation Process and Renewal
a. The App is a tool designed to assist healthcare practitioners in tracking and managing their revalidation process. It is not a substitute for professional judgment, and Revalidate is not responsible for the success or failure of your revalidation process and renewal.
b. Users are solely responsible for ensuring that all required documentation, worked hours, and relevant metrics are accurately recorded and submitted for revalidation.

8. Modifications to Terms
Revalidate reserves the right to modify these terms and conditions at any time. Continued use of the App after any such changes shall constitute your consent to such changes.

9. Company's Right to Audit Users
a. Revalidate reserves the right to audit user accounts to ensure compliance with these terms and conditions.
b. The audit may include a review of user data, usage patterns, and adherence to guidelines set forth by Revalidate.

10. Governing Law
These terms and conditions are governed by the laws of the United Kingdom.

11. User Conduct and Responsibilities
a. Users must comply with all applicable laws and regulations when using the App.
b. Users are responsible for the accuracy and legality of the information they input into the App.

12. Termination of Access
Revalidate reserves the right to terminate or suspend access to the App without notice if it believes, in its sole discretion, that a user has violated these terms or engaged in fraudulent or illegal activities.

13. Use of Questions from NMC and Other Government Bodies
a. Revalidate utilizes questions and materials from authoritative sources such as the Nursing and Midwifery Council (NMC) and other government bodies related to healthcare revalidation.
b. The questions provided in the App are for guidance purposes only and are not intended to replicate or infringe upon any copyright or intellectual property rights held by the NMC or other government bodies.
c. Users acknowledge that the questions provided in the App are sourced from public domain materials or used under fair use principles for educational and guidance purposes.
d. Revalidate does not claim ownership of the questions and materials obtained from NMC or other government bodies.

f. Revalidate is not responsible for any changes in NMC or government guidelines that may occur after the incorporation of questions into the App. Users are advised to independently verify information and adhere to the latest guidelines provided by the relevant authorities.

data.title: Privacy Policy
data.description:
ÔªøPrivacy Notice

Introduction

At Revalidate Ltd., we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Notice outlines how we collect, use, and safeguard the information you provide when using the Revalidate mobile application ("the App").

1. Information We Collect

a. Personal Information: When you register an account with Revalidate, we may collect personal information such as your name, email address, and other contact details.

b. Usage Data: We may collect information about how you use the App, including your interactions with features and functionalities.

c. Device Information: We may collect information about the device you use to access the App, including device type, operating system, and unique device identifiers.

2. How We Use Your Information

a. To Provide Services: We use the information collected to provide and maintain the functionality of the App, including user authentication, account management, and personalized content delivery.

b. To Improve Our Services: We may use usage data and feedback to analyse trends, track user engagement, and improve the performance and usability of the App.

c. To Communicate with You: We may use your contact information to send you important updates, notifications, and administrative messages related to your use of the App.

3. Data Security

a. We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to protect the security and confidentiality of your personal information.

b. Data is stored in a cloud environment using shared hosting services. The physical location of the data centre is not specified.

c. The developer has access to the database.

d. App Store and Play Store use their own encryption mechanisms for data in transit. On the API side, we use Laravel, which has a built-in authentication mechanism. Credentials are stored in an encrypted format using Laravel's encryption in a MySQL database.

e. We highly recommend that personally identifiable information (PII) is omitted unless absolutely necessary for the use of the App.

f. Despite our best efforts, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure. Therefore, we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

4. Data Sharing and Disclosure

a. We do not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer your personal information to third parties without your consent, except as required by law or legal process.

b. We may share your information with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the App, conducting our business, or servicing you, provided that such parties agree to keep this information confidential.

5. Data Retention

We will retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined in this Privacy Notice, or as required by applicable laws and regulations.

6. Children's Privacy

The App is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 16. If you are a parent or guardian and become aware that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately.

7. Changes to This Privacy Notice

We reserve the right to update or change this Privacy Notice at any time. Any changes will be effective immediately upon posting the updated Privacy Notice on this page.

8. Contact Us

If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Notice or our data practices, please contact us at revalidateapp@gmail.com.

9. Your Data Protection Rights

Depending on your location, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:

a. Access: You have the right to request copies of your personal data.

b. Rectification: You have the right to request that we correct any information you believe is inaccurate or complete information you believe is incomplete.

c. Erasure: You have the right to request that we erase your personal data, under certain conditions.

d. Restrict Processing: You have the right to request that we restrict the processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.

e. Object to Processing: You have the right to object to our processing of your personal data, under certain conditions.

f. Data Portability: You have the right to request that we transfer the data that we have collected to another organization, or directly to you, under certain conditions.

If you make a request, we have one month to respond to you. If you would like to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at our email: revalidateapp@gmail.com.

10. Third-Party Links

The App may contain links to other websites or services that are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third party's site. We strongly advise you to review the Privacy Policy of every site you visit. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for the content, privacy policies, or practices of any third- party sites or services.

11. International Data Transfers

Your information, including personal data, may be transferred to‚Äì and maintained on ‚Äì computers located outside of your state, province, country, or other governmental jurisdiction where the data protection laws may differ from those of your jurisdiction. If you are located outside the United Kingdom and choose to provide information to us, please note that we transfer the data, including personal data, to the United Kingdom and process it there.

12. Legal Basis for Processing Personal Data (For EEA Users)

If you are a user from the European Economic Area (EEA), our legal basis for collecting and using the personal information described in this Privacy Notice depends on the personal data we collect and the specific context in which we collect it. We may process your personal data because:

a. We need to perform a contract with you, such as when you use our App.

b. You have given us permission to do so.

c. The processing is in our legitimate interests and it's not overridden by your rights.

d. For payment processing purposes.

e. To comply with the law.

13. Data Accessibility and Deletion

a. If you cannot access your data, you can contact us at revalidateapp@gmail.com for assistance. We hold all access to the App, database, and source code.

b. We will delete user data permanently as soon as the user requests deletion through the App. The data deletion process is initiated immediately upon request.

14. Open Source and Code Reviews

a. We use open-source technologies including Laravel for the API, MySQL for the database, and React Native for the hybrid mobile app.

b. We conduct manual code reviews and testing to ensure the integrity and security of our applications.

15. Independent Testing and Penetration Tests

a. Currently, we do not employ independent testers or use automated tools for code/application testing.

b. We perform manual testing and validation to ensure the application's security and functionality.

By using the Revalidate App, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Privacy Notice. If you do not agree with any part of this Notice, please refrain from using the App.

What are cookies?
Cookies are small text files that are placed on your computer, smartphone or other devices when you access the internet.


Why are cookies essential to the Revalidate App?
This App, along with many others, uses cookies. Cookies let users navigate around sites and (where appropriate), let us tailor the content to fit the needs of our site's visitors. Without cookies enabled we cannot guarantee that the App and your experience of it are as we intended it to be.


None of the cookies we use to collect your personal information and they cannot be used to identify you.


Types of cookies
The length of time a cookie stays on your device depends on its type. We use two types of cookies on our App.

  • Session (Transient) cookies: these cookies are erased when you close your browser and do not collect information from your computer. They typically store information in the form of a session identification that does not personally identify the user.

  • Persistent (Permanent/Stored) cookies: these cookies are stored on your hard drive until they expire (i.e., based on a set expiration date) or until you delete them. These cookies are used to collect identifying information about the user, such as Web surfing behaviour or user preferences for a specific site.

ANY QUESTIONS?

If you have a question, of any type, about Revalidate App, our Privacy Notice or the use to which we put the information we gather, please contact us via email. Details below.

HOW TO CONTACT THE REVALIDATE TEAM:
Email: revalidateapp@gmail.com
Social media: Instagram revalidate_app

Review of this notice: Revalidate keeps this Privacy Notice under regular review.
This Privacy Notice was last updated in May 2024.

data.title: About Us
data.description:
Our story


Hi, my name is Sarah and this app was born out of my own experiences as a dedicated nurse who understood the challenges of managing the revalidation process. Faced with the need to keep track of work hours, CPD (Continuing Professional Development) activities, and various aspects of the revalidation journey, I was determined to find a solution. So, I embarked on a journey to create an app that would not only meet my own needs but also benefit countless other healthcare professionals facing similar circumstances.

Revalidate is a tracker app designed specifically for healthcare practitioners in the United Kingdom. It streamlines the revalidation process by providing an all-in-one, user-friendly platform focused on extreme efficiency. From storing work hours to documenting CPD activities and earnings, Revalidate ensures that professionals have all the relevant data at hand to complete their revalidation effortlessly and efficiently. In addition to core features, such as tracking metrics and storing documentation, Revalidate also offers useful extras like a calendar, notes section, and timer, providing comprehensive support for various documentation types that users may want to record.

Our mission at Revalidate is to remove the stress and tedium from the revalidation process, giving healthcare professionals more time to focus on their essential duties. Whether you're a nurse, doctor, or any other healthcare professional, our app is tailored to meet your needs. Revalidate is designed to
simplify the process and empower healthcare professionals like you to stay organized and on track.

Key Features:
1. Work Hours:
Log in any job you undertake.
Automatically calculates the hours and earnings.

2. CPD Hours:
Log in any training you participate in.
Automatically calculates the CPD hours.

3. Calendar:
Enter future work or training commitments.

4. Timer:
Track work hours with precision.
Press start when you begin work and stop when you finish.
Shows time spent and allows easy logging into work hours.

5. Earnings:
Conveniently calculate earnings, particularly beneficial for self-employed professionals.

6. Feedback Log:
Log any feedback received, providing essential proof for revalidation.

7. Reflective Account Form:
Create and store notes for work or training reflections.

8. Discussion:
Keep records of any discussions made, valuable for the revalidation process.

9. Gallery:
Upload and organize training certificates, payslips, feedback proof, and more.

Thank you for choosing Revalidate to support your revalidation journey.
Please use the contact button if you have any further questions and check out revalidate_app on instagram for instruction videos.

data.title: FAQ
data.description:
FAQ

Q: What if my place of work is not listed?
A: Select ‚Äòother‚Äô and add name in notes or contact us to include to app.

Q: I am not required by NMC to complete an appraisal. Do I have to complete everything in the app?
A: No, The app is designed for a variety of healthcare workers and you are only required to
complete what is applicable to you.

Q: I do not see my profession listed, Can I still use the app?
A: Yes, The app is designed for multi-functional personal use.

Q: I have completed my hours, How do I reset the app?
A: Once the criteria has been met, the app will automatically reset at the revalidation due date. You can also delete any previous entries.

Q: Can I directly send my app data to NMC?
A: No, the app cannot act as proof of what you have entered. If you are selected for audit fromany of the governing bodies, you would still need confirmation from the source.

Please contact us if you have any further queries.
